      <abstract>
        <p>Testimony of Walter Löbner, which became a part of the Documentation campaign, Prague.
          Löbner was arrested by the Gestapo in April 1939 for his antifascist views, then he was
          imprisoned in several concentration camps (Sachsenhausen, Oranienburg, Auschwitz, Dora).
          In his testimony he is listing particular names of several Gestapo and SS members, who
          were especially cruel to the prisoners. He describes their behaviour and methods of
          torturing the inmates.</p>
      </abstract>


