      <p>Extract from the Statement of Dr <persName ref="#ehri_et_lobner_walter">Walter
          Löbner</persName>, born <date when="1903-01-27">27.1.1903</date></p>

      <p>In the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-88" type="camp"
          >Ellrich im Harz</placeName>
        <term type="keyword" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567"
          >camp</term>, the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567">camp</term>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477"
          >commandant</term>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">SS
          Oberscharführer</term>
        <persName ref="#ehri_et_brinkmann_otto">Brinkmann</persName> forced a <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject"
          >prisoner</term> who had been accused on <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-6922" type="subject"
          >cannibalism</term> to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832"
          type="subject">eat</term> human body parts in front of witness, even having salt and
        pepper passed to him. On the same day, he had the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject"
          >prisoner</term>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745"
          >killed</term>.</p>


      <p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2884403/kremmen.html">Kremmen</placeName>, <date
          when="1945-05-14">14.5.1945</date></p>

      <p>
        <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657"
          type="subject">Dokumentační akce</term>
        <date when="1945-08-26">26.VIII.1945</date>
      </p>

      <p>
        <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Zeev Scheck</persName>
      </p>

      <pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-JMP017_02.jpg"/>
      <p>Transcript</p>

      <p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2884403/kremmen.html">Kremmen</placeName>, <date
          when="1945-05-14">14.5.1945</date></p>

      <p>I, Dr <persName ref="#ehri_et_lobner_walter">Walter Löbner</persName>, born <date
          when="1903-01-27">27.01.1903</date> in <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3075843/hermanova-hut.html">Hermannshütte</placeName> in
          <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077311/czechia.html">Bohemia</placeName>, a
          <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html"
          >Czechoslovak</placeName>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1147"
          >citizen</term>, last living at <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>-<placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Vinohrady</placeName>, <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Fochova</placeName> 9, was <term
          type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598"
          >arrested</term> by the <orgName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-003045">Prague Gestapo</orgName>
        on <date when="1939-04-18">18.04.1939</date> and imprisoned in several different <term
          type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496">concentration
          camps</term> in <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159">Germany</term> (<placeName
          type="camp" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-803"
          >Sachsenhausen</placeName>, <placeName type="camp"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-847">Oranienburg</placeName>,
          <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp"
          >Auschwitz</placeName>, <placeName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-3" type="camp">Auschwitz
          3</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-433"
          type="camp">Gross Rosen</placeName>, <placeName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-70" type="camp">Dora</placeName>,
          <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-88" type="camp">Ellrich
          im Harz</placeName>, <placeName type="camp"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-847">Oranienburg</placeName>)
        until I was able to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204"
          type="subject">escape</term> to freedom on <date when="1945-04-21">21.04.1945</date>. At
        the moment, I am in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2884403/kremmen.html"
          >Kremmen</placeName>, because the garrison and population is without a <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">doctor</term>,
        and I am employed as the head <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">doctor</term>
        in a newly founded city <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-282"
          type="subject">hospital</term>.</p>

      <p>Until the loss of the <placeName ref="#ehri_et_sudeten">Sudetenland</placeName> and the
        occupation by the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159">Germans</term>, I was a
          <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject"
          >doctor</term> and surgeon in <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3071024/marianske-lazne.html">Marianské Lázně</placeName> and
        the interim head of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-282"
          type="subject">hospital</term> there. I made no secret of my <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-968">antifascist</term> opinions
        which, in <date when="1939-04">April 1939</date>, let my <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598">arrest</term>. The <term
          type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598">arrest</term>
        warrant stated the reason for my imprisonment as <q>strong suspicion of high treason against
          the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159"
            >German</term> people</q>.</p>

      <p>During the six-year path of martyrdom and suffering, I had the opportunity to learn about
        the terrible, sadistic methods of the <orgName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> and the
          <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
          >SS</term>, both first-hand and by observation. As I want to play my part in making sure
        that those responsible are punished, I want to make the names of several perpetrators that I
        know available to the commendable investigating authorities.</p>
      <p> 1. The <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350"
          >Gestapo</orgName> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
          type="subject">SS man</term>, Commissioner <persName ref="#ehri_et_wigger_hubert"
          >Wiggers</persName> of the <orgName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-003045">Prague Gestapo</orgName>,
        who imprisoned me and sent me to the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration
          camp</term> without affording me – a <term type="subject"
          ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_czechs">Czech</term>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1147"
          >citizen</term> – the right to a proper <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130">trial</term>.</p>
      <p>2. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject"
          >SS man</term> and director of the <orgName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669"
          >prison</term>
        <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3068601/pankrac.html">Pankrac</placeName> in
          <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>, by the
        name of <persName ref="#ehri_et_zoppa">Zoppa</persName> or something similar, who often
        terrorised the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483"
          type="subject">prisoners</term> personally with beatings. He broke two of my ribs on <date
          when="1939-09-16">16.09.1939</date> by punching me.</p>
      <p>3. The <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119"
          >policeman</term>
        <persName ref="#ehri_et_bohlke_max">Max Böhlke</persName> – or something similar – from
          <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2879139/leipzig.html">Leipzig</placeName> who was
        a prison guard and burst my eardrum by punching me whilst I was in <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669">prison</term> in <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>, and as a result I
        got a terrible middle ear <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292">infection</term>, and lost my
        hearing.</p>
      <p>4. In the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496"
          >concentration camp</term>
        <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-803" type="camp"
          >Sachsenhausen</placeName>
        <placeName type="camp" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-847"
          >Oranienburg</placeName> near <placeName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/jc-places-place-jmp-1085">Berlin</placeName>,
        the following <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">SS men</term> who are known
        to me by name and whose unheard of brutality – both physical and mental – was an outrage to
        even the most primitive requirements of a <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650">prisoner</term>’s human
        rights: <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
          >Oberscharführer</term>
        <persName ref="#ehri_et_bugdahle">Bugdahle</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_ficker_fritz"
          >Fickert</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_van_deezen">Van Deezen</persName>, <persName
          ref="#ehri_et_birke">Birke</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_kaiser">Kaiser</persName>,
          <persName ref="#ehri_et_schubert_wilhelm">Schubert</persName>, <persName
          ref="#ehri_et_brumm_karl">Brumm</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_sorge_gustav">Gustav
          Sorge</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_sinke">Sinke</persName>, <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477">Camp Commandant</term>
        <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-001244"
          >Schwarzhuber</persName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2867714/munich.html"
          >Munich</placeName> who was later the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477">commandant</term> in
          <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2" type="camp"
          >Birkenau</placeName>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477"
          type="subject">Commandant</term>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
          >Sturmbannführer</term> Heydrich later <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477">Commandant</term>
        <orgName ref="#ehri_et_heinkel_werke_oranienburg">Heinkel-Oranienburg</orgName>. They have,
        along with many others whose names I don’t know, contributed to, or directly caused, the
          <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject"
          >deaths</term> of thousands of innocent <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483">people</term> through
        beatings with their fists and sticks, through so-called <q>sport</q> and other torments, the
        withholding of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832"
          type="subject">food</term> and were also involved in the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killing</term>
        of many <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_russians">Russian</term>
        <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511" type="subject">prisoners
          of war</term> in the summer and autumn of <date when="1941">1941</date>.</p>
      <p>5. <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
          >Sturmführer</term>
        <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000187"
        >Höss</persName>(name unknown) in <date when="1940">1940</date> the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477">camp commandant</term> in
          <placeName type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-803"
          >Sachsenhausen</placeName> and later in <placeName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp"
          >Auschwitz</placeName>, is the person responsible for the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518">deportation</term> and <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killing</term>
        by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-534" type="subject"
          >gas</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-570"
          type="subject">starvation</term> of one and a half million <term type="subject"
          ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_hungarians">Hungarian</term>, <term type="subject"
          ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_romanians">Romanian</term>, <term type="subject"
          ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_slovaks">Slovakian</term>, <term type="subject"
          ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_italians">Italian</term> and <term type="subject"
          ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_greeks">Greek</term> Jews.</p>
      <p>6. For the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532">killing</term> by <term
          type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-570"
          >starvation</term>, terror, epidemics, <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-534">gas</term>, <term
          type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532"
          >shooting</term>, beating, torture and similar of 7 million Jews from the other countries
        of Europe and many hundreds of thousands of non-Jews in the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496">camps</term> of <placeName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp"
          >Auschwitz</placeName> and <placeName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2" type="camp"
          >Birkenau</placeName>, the following <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">SS men</term> are <pb n="3"
          facs="EHRI-ET-JMP017_03.jpg"/> guilty: the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477">camp commandants</term>
        <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000587"
          >Auemier</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_schwarz">Schwarz</persName>, <persName
          ref="#ehri_et_fritzsch_karl">Fritsch</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_hossler_franz"
          >Hessler</persName>, <persName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000019">Baer</persName>,
          <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-001244"
          >Schwarzhuber</persName>, <persName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000187">Höss</persName>.</p>
      <p>7. In the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-506"
          >women’s camp</term>, <placeName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1" type="camp">Auschwitz
          I</placeName>
        <placeName type="camp" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-22"
          >Harmense</placeName>, the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">female</term>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">SS</term>
        <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-478" type="subject"
          >guard</term> Major <persName ref="#ehri_et_rendel_klein">Rendel</persName> (name unknown)
        née <persName ref="#ehri_et_rendel_klein">Klein</persName> was involved in the harassment
        and physical and mental abuse of the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">female</term>
        <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject"
          >prisoners</term> and is to blame for the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">deaths</term>
        of many.</p>
      <p>8. The same is true for the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">women’s
          concentration camp</term>
        <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1" type="camp">Auschwitz
          1</placeName>
        <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-10" type="camp"
          >Budy</placeName> and the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">female</term>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">SS</term>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-478"
          >guard</term> Frau <persName ref="#ehri_et_hasse_elisabeth">Hasse</persName> from
          <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2918987/goerlitz.html">Görlitz</placeName>, who
        was later the head of <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556">labour</term> in the <term
          type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-506">women’s
          camp</term>
        <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Birkenau</placeName>
        and took part in the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411">selections</term> of <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>
        who were no longer able to <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556">work</term> and so
        contributed to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745"
          type="subject">deaths</term> of many <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject"
        >women</term>.</p>
      <p>9. The following so-called <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">doctors</term>
        from the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
          >SS</term> made personal decisions about <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killing</term>
        hundreds of thousands of <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483">people</term> who were unable
        to <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556"
          >work</term> but also completely healthy <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483">people</term> through the use
        of phenol injections into the heart, <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-534" type="subject">gas</term>, by
        being burnt alive, use in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-495"
          type="subject">experimental</term> operations as medical guinea pigs, etc. <term
          type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
          >Sturmbannführer</term> Dr <persName ref="#ehri_et_wirths_eduard">Wirths</persName>
        (spelling unknown), <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">Hauptsturmführer</term> Dr
          <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000272"
          >Mengele</persName>, <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">Hauptsturmführer</term> Dr
          <persName ref="#ehri_et_fischer_horst">Fischer</persName>, <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">Sturmführer</term> Dr
          <persName ref="#ehri_et_rohde_werner">Rode</persName>, <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">Sturmführer</term> Dr
          <persName ref="#ehri_et_klein_fritz">Klein</persName>, <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">Sturmführer</term> Dr
          <persName ref="#ehri_et_konig_hans_wilhelm">König</persName>, Dr <persName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-001266">Lucas</persName>, Dr
          <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-001165"
          >Thilo</persName>.</p>
      <p>10. The mutilation of living <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483">persons</term> through <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-668" type="subject"
          >sterilisation</term>, castration and similar operations were carried out particularly by
        the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-404"
          >Luftwaffe</orgName>
        <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject"
          >doctor</term>, <persName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000824">Schumann</persName> or a
        name similar to that.</p>
      <p>11. In the so-called <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">women</term>’s block of the
          <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject"
          >men</term>’s <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567">camp</term>
        <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1" type="camp">Auschwitz
          1</placeName>, thousands of healthy <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>
        were mutilated by injections, exposure to radiation and operations and later violently <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject"
          >murdered</term>, for which the nine or ten named <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">doctors</term>
        are responsible.</p>
      <p>12. Involved in the mass shootings in Block 11 of the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration
          camp</term>
        <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp"
          >Auschwitz</placeName> were <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS
          Oberscharführer</term>
        <persName ref="#ehri_et_kleeman_hermann">Kleemann</persName>– later the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">camp
          commandant</term> in <placeName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1272" type="camp"
          >Janina</placeName> and <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">SS Unterscharführer</term>
        <persName ref="#ehri_et_schmidt_max">Schmidt</persName> (spelling unknown) from <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/2842647/saarbruecken.html">Saarbrücken</placeName>.</p>
      <p>13. <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
          >Oberscharführer</term>
        <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaue_bernhard">Glaue</persName>, <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477">camp commandant</term> in
          <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1" type="camp"
          >Auschwitz 1</placeName>
        <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-10" type="camp"
          >Budy</placeName> is responsible for the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532">deaths</term> of many <term
          type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483">people</term>
        through physical stress and forcing them to work 19-hour <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work
          days</term> without sufficient nutrition.</p>
      <p>14. As the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567">camp</term>
        <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp"
          >Auschwitz</placeName>, <placeName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2" type="camp"
          >Birkenau</placeName> was emptied in <date when="1945-01">January 1945</date> due to the
        advance of the victorious <orgName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Red Army</orgName> and the
          <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483"
          >prisoners</term> were deported to <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159">Germany</term>, <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS
          Rottenführer</term>
        <persName ref="#ehri_et_niemeier_albert">Niemeier</persName> from <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/2910831/hannover.html">Hannover</placeName>
        <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject"
          >shot</term>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483"
          >prisoners</term> in the neck and left their bodies where they fell on the 18-day <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">march</term>
        from <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-3" type="camp"
          >Auschwitz 3</placeName>
        <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1272" type="camp"
          >Janina</placeName> to <placeName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-433" type="camp">Gross
          Rosen</placeName> in <placeName ref="#ehri_et_silesia">Silesia</placeName> if they were no
        longer able to walk.</p>
      <p>15. In the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-88"
          type="camp">Ellrich</placeName>
        <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject"
          >camp</term> in Harz, the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477">camp commandant</term>, <term
          type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">SS
          Oberscharführer</term>
        <persName ref="#ehri_et_brinkmann_otto">Brinkmann</persName>, forced a <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject"
          >prisoner</term> who had been accused on <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-6922" type="subject"
          >cannibalism</term> to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832"
          type="subject">eat</term> human body parts in front of witnesses, even having salt and
        pepper passed to him. On the same day, he had the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject"
          >prisoner</term>
        <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject"
          >killed</term>.</p>
      <p>16. As the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-88"
          type="camp">Ellrich</placeName>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567"
          >camp</term> in Harz was forced to <orgName ref="#ehri_et_heinkel_werke_oranienburg"
          >Heikel-Oranienburg</orgName> in <date when="1945">1945</date>, the leader of the
        transport, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
          type="subject">Oberscharführer</term>
        <persName ref="#ehri_et_gaudeck_karl">Gaudeck</persName>, was responsible for the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term>
        of many hundreds of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483"
          type="subject">prisoners</term> due to insufficient distribution of <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832">food</term>.</p>
      <p>17.This is just a small excerpt of the horrific catalogue of guilt of <persName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000185">Hitler</persName>’s dogs
        of Hell and many names as I can remember. The number of the innocent <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">dead</term> is
        without end, including my whole <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">family</term>, my parents and
        siblings and I can be considered some kind of wonder of the world, that I managed to survive
        the past 6 years of the most terrible mental, spiritual, physical and sexual distress, and,
        in the last hours – through a brave <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escape</term>
        over the wire – was able to avoid physical annihilation. To the public prosecutors, who
        might perhaps be helped by this indictment document, I would like to say one sentence, that
        I often recited in the shadow of the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">gas
          chambers</term> in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0"
          type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName> and <placeName type="camp"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Birkenau</placeName>, as I
        wanted to collapse from anger, suffering and torment and only the thought of vengeance kept
        be going: <q><term type="subject"
            ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745">Death</term> is no
          punishment.</q>
      </p>


